To me, these are one of the most functional styles Lululemon makes as the have a zipper pocket in back (great for storing keys/id if your hiking or running), a pocket on either side of the leg (great for your phone on a jog, teaching a class or private) and the are 28" so they are long enough that they come to my ankles.
The are one or the more compressive styles (which I love), but not to compressive.
I have the brushed fabric in black and dark adobe, while I have the regular fabric in Midnight Navy, Dark Grey, Datk Olive and Tiny Tooth.
I only wish ya'll would do some of the cool camo and other misc. prints on this style.

column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column6: Until this year I have not had any problems with any of my lulu clothing and raved about the brand to my friends for years. However, recently I have been really disappointed with the quality of lulu's products. I bought a pair of these tights less than a month ago and they already have a hole in the knee (I did not snag them on anything), some of the seams are starting to come undone and there is some signs of wear on the material at the top of my right thigh. I have always taken really good care of my lulu clothing as it is so expensive and I am on a student budget so I need to last so I do not understand what is going on. But I am really not impressed and am quite disappointed by the quality of these tights. Besides the poor quality, I really like the fit and style of these tights. The stitching is very flattering and the side pockets are the perfect place to slip your phone in when you are going for a run. But, if you don't have money to burn, I would not recommend these tights as they didn't even last a month for me and I am scared to wear them now because I do not want to make the hole any bigger. I really hope lulu steps their quality game back up, as I find it super frustrating to spend so much money on a pair of tights to only be able to wear them for less than a month.

column6:

I ordered them online in a size 4 (5'2", 140lbs) and when I got them I decided to keep them thinking they would loosen up over time, which they have, but not as much as I thought. I do really love them though. I always have issues with Lulu leggings getting loose and pilled and these haven't so far which is good.
Another thing I've noticed is they're thin. This could just be because they're tight, but my underwear lines show through them, even with the Namastay Put Thongs from Lulu.
I also have noticed that they're not very warm even though they're "brushed". The material doesn't feel like an older pair of brushed leggings I had and sadly had to exchange because they were chafing (an older version of the Brushed Speed Tights).
My dream is to find a pair of actually warm thicker pair of leggings that fit perfectly and I will buy them up.

column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column6: I have had these for about a year and love them! You can put your phone (I have the big iPhone) in the leg pocket and by some miracle, it doesn't pull the pants down. column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column6: Seriously. You'll want to size up. I bought two pairs in my typical size 6 like every other full length Lululemon legging I own and I struggle to get them on. They are so tight they leave dig marks on my skin, hoping they'll stretch out eventually. Other than that it's a great legging, the pockets lay smooth and they're still in great shape after a few washes.

column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column6:
I have multiple pairs of Lulu leggings and these instantly became my new favorite pair to work out in - I've found they compress everything a little more than other Full On Luxtreme pants I have, but they aren't too tight. They're flattering, very comfortable and they stay up well through cardio, HIIT and weightlifting sessions. I was super excited about these leggings, BUT now after the first wash (hand wash cycle with only other Lulu items and air-dried)...the seams have already started to unravel in the crotch, which was extremely disappointing. For a more expensive pair of leggings (and considering the great fit overall), I was really hoping that these would be better quality without already starting to come undone after one wash :(
Overall I still think they're great in terms of fit and feel, but the underlying quality in the seams/make is lacking for me - at least in the pair I own :/ Hopefully other pairs in the future will not have this stitching issue!

I've also washed them a couple times and haven't had any issues with the seams, or the material being see through. I would absolutely recommend trying these crops. column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column6: Have the heathered deep coal color. Love the fit of them. They stay up and in place, and offer enough support for the big muscle groups. I thought these were supposed to wick away moisture! Talk about embarrassing. I was mortified. DO NOT BUY if you plan on sweating in them as they don't wick away sweat and they get super dark when wet.

column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"

column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column5: WHAT IS GOING ON WITH SIZING?!
column6: I have these exact same pants in another color, same size 4 and they fit snug, but good compression for running gear. I just ordered a second pair in the heathered black color and I could barely squeeze myself into them. It was an effort to get them over my butt. I have the tight stuff pants, and they're not this tight!!! It was like I was wearing a completely different pair of pants! How is it possible that Lulu's pants vary THAT dramatically just from purchasing a different color. This isn't the first time I've had this problem, and I honestly think it's absolutely ridiculous that you can't seem to nail down uniform sizing in a pair of running pants. Unfortunately, back they go.

column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column6:
I'm not sure if I just got lucky??? because I love these tights and I can see that other customers have not been satisfied with them. I have only had mine 6 weeks, but in that time I'm ashamed to say, I have probably worn them at least 20 times. I wash them after each wear, and throw them in the dryer for 5 minutes on delicate, then hang to finish drying. I love how they look, I love how they feel, and they are very comfortable. A lot of my other tights start to fall down, but these ones stay put. I never have to pull or readjust. I LOVE the pockets. In this day and age when we all have our cell phones with us at all times I don't know how women can stand wearing tights without pockets. I will only purchase tights with pockets and these ones have one on each side which holds my cell and epipen perfectly and also a zippered pocket at the waist. I purchased the brushed tights but you have to use your imagination that they are brushed. Do not purchase if you think they are fleecy or extra soft since they are not. It would be great if they were brushed more significantly because they do not offer much protection from wind or cold. I love these so much I will be purchasing another pair.
Thanks Lulu!

column1: Speed Up Tight Full-On Luxtreme Brushed 28"
column6: Bought these pants two weeks ago and I was completely in love with them. I washed them exactly according the lulu website instructions and when I took them out of the washing machine I noticed that they have two small holes in the pant near the knee area. Extremely dissatisfied as I paid $133 for these pants which I cannot wear anymore. This has never happened to any of my other Lulu pants and is highly upsetting to have this happen. Do not waste your money on these leggings.
